# SELECT CUSTOM SETTING

The **IMAGE QUALITY SETTING > SELECT CUSTOM SETTING** item (item â‘ ) shows the current custom settings bank:

- **BASE**: No custom settings bank selected.
- **C1â€“C7**: Select a bank to view the settings saved using the **IMAGE QUALITY SETTING > EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING** option.
- **C1â€“C7**: The current custom settings bank.

## Viewing and Changing Settings

1. Press **Q** to display the quick menu during shooting.

   !Quick Menu Display

2. Use the focus stick (focus lever) to highlight items and rotate the rear command dial to change.
   - Changes are not saved to the current settings bank.
   - Settings that differ from those in the current settings bank (**C1â€“C7**) are shown in red.

   !Focus Stick and Command Dial

3. Press **Q** to exit when settings are complete.

> ðŸ’¡ **Note:**  
> The quick menu can also be edited using touch controls.
